19
00:00:18,606 --> 00:00:19,732
<i>Water wars!</i>

20
00:00:19,941 --> 00:00:23,319
<i>Tensions run high on the ocean world
of Mon Calamari</i>

21
00:00:23,402 --> 00:00:25,404
<i>where two separate peoples,</i>

22
00:00:25,446 --> 00:00:27,448
<i>the aggressive squid-like Quarren,</i>

23
00:00:27,490 --> 00:00:29,617
<i>and their peaceful neighbor,
the Mon Calamari,</i>

24
00:00:29,700 --> 00:00:32,370
<i>struggle to maintain a fragile coexistence.</i>

25
00:00:32,787 --> 00:00:33,913
<i>Adding to this strife,</i>

26
00:00:33,955 --> 00:00:38,084
<i>the king of the Mon Calamari
has been found mysteriously murdered,</i>

27
00:00:38,459 --> 00:00:42,463
<i>leaving his young son Prince Lee-Char
to guide his people alone.</i>

28
00:00:42,797 --> 00:00:46,634
<i>But the Quarren race will not accept
the new ruler as their king.</i>

29
00:00:47,093 --> 00:00:51,806
<i>Senator Amidala and her Jedi bodyguard
have arrived to help resolve the matter</i>

30
00:00:51,889 --> 00:00:55,309
<i>and to avoid plunging the planet
into civil war.</i>

31
00:00:59,146 --> 00:01:01,857
You've all prospered under our rule!

32
00:01:01,941 --> 00:01:03,401
It's time for a change!

33
00:01:03,484 --> 00:01:05,987
The prince's rule has been preordained!

34
00:01:06,028 --> 00:01:07,697
Down with this monarchy!

35
00:01:07,780 --> 00:01:10,992
We'll defend our right for a Mon Cala king!

36
00:01:11,117 --> 00:01:14,537
-We want a Quarren king !
-Down with the Mon Cala!

37
00:01:14,745 --> 00:01:16,372
Power to the Quarren!

38
00:01:16,455 --> 00:01:19,083
I am dedicated to serving the Quarren

39
00:01:19,166 --> 00:01:21,836
as well as my own people,
the Mon Calamari.

40
00:01:21,877 --> 00:01:23,004
Silence!

41
00:01:23,045 --> 00:01:26,173
You haven't earned the right
to speak at this gathering!

42
00:01:26,215 --> 00:01:28,634
You have no say
in the matter, Ambassador,

43
00:01:28,676 --> 00:01:31,512
you are only here as an observer
for the Separatists.

44
00:01:32,263 --> 00:01:36,183
Do not forget I am here
at the request of the Quarren

45
00:01:36,225 --> 00:01:40,813
because you, Captain,
demanded the presence of the Republic.

46
00:01:43,316 --> 00:01:44,942
Such a disgrace,

47
00:01:45,026 --> 00:01:47,028
I'll give you a lesson in manners.

48
00:01:48,237 --> 00:01:51,157
Prince Lee-Char will bring the planet
to ruin!

49
00:01:51,532 --> 00:01:55,536
The boy has neither the experience
nor the knowledge to lead.

50
00:01:55,745 --> 00:01:58,331
Please, you're here to find a compromise.

51
00:01:58,831 --> 00:02:01,250
What can the Republic do
to help keep the peace?

52
00:02:01,667 --> 00:02:04,920
This is a matter between
the Quarren and the Mon Cala.

53
00:02:05,004 --> 00:02:06,589
Yeah, who asked you?

54
00:02:06,714 --> 00:02:10,551
-The Republic has no place here!
-Down with the Republic!

55
00:02:17,933 --> 00:02:22,438
We refuse to support the coronation
of another Mon Cala king.

56
00:02:23,064 --> 00:02:24,398
I'm sorry.

57
00:02:24,732 --> 00:02:25,733
Ambassador?

58
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:30,821
It is my opinion the Quarren
have no further business here.

59
00:02:39,413 --> 00:02:43,000
Come on, Captain Ackbar,
we have to contact Master Yoda.

60
00:02:47,088 --> 00:02:49,882
Your father was my trusted friend.

61
00:02:50,591 --> 00:02:53,761
I am sorry for your loss.

62
00:03:07,942 --> 00:03:10,111
<i>This civil war, is it inevitable?</i>

63
00:03:10,528 --> 00:03:12,738
Sadly so, Master Yoda.

64
00:03:12,780 --> 00:03:15,282
The Separatist ambassador
came here to stir up the Quarren

65
00:03:15,324 --> 00:03:17,243
and that's exactly what he did.

66
00:03:17,284 --> 00:03:20,663
It's only a matter of time before
the Quarren withdraw from the Republic.

67
00:03:20,746 --> 00:03:24,208
<i>I suspect behind this, Count Dooku is.</i>

68
00:03:24,291 --> 00:03:27,128
<i>The Mon Calamari system
is still part of the Republic.</i>

69
00:03:27,169 --> 00:03:29,797
<i>This planet
must not fall into Separatist hands.</i>

70
00:03:29,839 --> 00:03:32,216
<i>I'll dispatch Master Fisto
and your Padawan, Tano,</i>

71
00:03:32,299 --> 00:03:33,592
<i>along with a company of clones,</i>

72
00:03:34,009 --> 00:03:36,303
<i>they'll be at your side by day's end.</i>

73
00:03:36,387 --> 00:03:37,596
<i>In the meantime, Captain,</i>

74
00:03:37,638 --> 00:03:41,100
<i>assemble the Mon Cala troops
and prepare for a Quarren assault.</i>

75
00:04:07,626 --> 00:04:09,754
The troops are being assembled, Senator.

76
00:04:10,254 --> 00:04:13,048
Let's hope we don't need them, Captain.

77
00:04:13,132 --> 00:04:17,386
I'm entrusting the safety
of Prince Lee-Char to your hands.

78
00:04:17,762 --> 00:04:23,100
You must remain at his side
at all times as his personal bodyguard.

79
00:04:23,517 --> 00:04:25,060
Senator, if the boy is to...

80
00:04:25,144 --> 00:04:28,230
We are on the verge of a civil war, Captain.

81
00:04:28,355 --> 00:04:33,110
And that boy is the Supreme Commander
of Mon Cala's military.

82
00:04:33,194 --> 00:04:38,199
It's up to you to see that he remains safe
and that he can handle the job.

83
00:04:38,324 --> 00:04:42,369
With due respect, Senator,
the prince is not ready to lead an army.

84
00:04:42,453 --> 00:04:43,871
He needs training.

85
00:04:44,038 --> 00:04:46,373
You have your orders, Captain.

86
00:04:49,543 --> 00:04:52,755
You are right, Captain,
I am not trained to lead an army.

87
00:04:52,838 --> 00:04:56,050
Come on, Your Highness,
we have a war to win.

88
00:05:23,077 --> 00:05:25,955
The army has assembled, Count Dooku.

89
00:05:26,330 --> 00:05:30,000
<i>Well done, Tamson.
What about the Quarren leader?</i>

90
00:05:30,084 --> 00:05:33,796
The Quarren leader is on board 100%.

91
00:05:33,879 --> 00:05:38,425
He will deliver the planet into your hands
just as you said he would.

92
00:05:38,843 --> 00:05:40,094
<i>Very good, Commander,</i>

93
00:05:40,177 --> 00:05:43,931
<i>in the end, control of this planet
will be in your hands.</i>

94
00:05:44,431 --> 00:05:46,100
<i>Proceed as planned.</i>

95
00:05:54,900 --> 00:05:59,446
In this time of crisis,
our king has something to say.

96
00:06:00,239 --> 00:06:02,616
I know many of you agree with the Quarren,

97
00:06:02,658 --> 00:06:04,618
that I am too young to rule.

98
00:06:04,702 --> 00:06:08,414
But I assure you I will use
all my strength and all my abilities

99
00:06:08,455 --> 00:06:10,749
to lead us through this challenge.

100
00:06:11,125 --> 00:06:12,877
We are a great people,

101
00:06:12,960 --> 00:06:16,630
and I will do all I can
to negotiate peace without bloodshed.

102
00:06:16,714 --> 00:06:19,133
I do not believe the Quarren will attack.

103
00:06:28,642 --> 00:06:29,810
Attack!

104
00:06:43,324 --> 00:06:45,576
-It's an attack!
-Take cover.

105
00:06:55,002 --> 00:06:58,505
-The prince! The prince is here!
-He's joining the battle.

106
00:06:59,340 --> 00:07:00,507
Captain!

107
00:07:00,549 --> 00:07:02,426
What are your orders, Your Highness?

108
00:07:03,844 --> 00:07:05,930
Stay where you are and hold the line.

109
00:07:06,597 --> 00:07:08,724
If I may suggest, Captain,

110
00:07:08,807 --> 00:07:12,645
we should take the prince to a safer place
until the Republic reinforcements arrive.

111
00:07:12,686 --> 00:07:16,357
That's impossible.
That is a decision only the prince can make.

112
00:07:16,398 --> 00:07:18,609
He is our leader.

113
00:07:20,361 --> 00:07:21,362
This is horrible.

114
00:07:21,737 --> 00:07:24,907
Your Highness, this is not a wise decision.

115
00:07:24,990 --> 00:07:26,075
And you know it.

116
00:07:26,450 --> 00:07:28,535
Forget your tradition. This is war!

117
00:07:29,912 --> 00:07:30,913
Majesty?

118
00:07:32,831 --> 00:07:36,877
I have to stay here with my people.
Press your attack, Captain.

119
00:08:00,901 --> 00:08:04,238
Soldiers of Mon Calamari,
this is your home.

120
00:08:04,613 --> 00:08:06,198
Do not let it fall!

121
00:08:13,122 --> 00:08:16,750
I need to get some troops
behind those Separatist droids.

122
00:08:16,834 --> 00:08:18,877
Come on, I know a shortcut.

123
00:08:30,764 --> 00:08:33,350
-We should come out right behind them.
-Good plan.

124
00:08:34,226 --> 00:08:35,227
Look out!

125
00:08:41,483 --> 00:08:42,568
What do we do now?

126
00:08:42,651 --> 00:08:44,445
Well, we got to come up with another plan.

127
00:08:45,946 --> 00:08:46,947
Any ideas?

128
00:08:47,031 --> 00:08:51,201
Our only choice now
is to wait for the Jedi reinforcements.

129
00:08:56,373 --> 00:08:58,125
Blue Leader, standing by.

130
00:08:58,542 --> 00:09:00,335
Red Leader, standing by.

131
00:09:06,800 --> 00:09:08,969
All squadrons are in position, General Fisto.

132
00:09:09,011 --> 00:09:10,429
<i>You may deploy when ready.</i>

133
00:09:10,471 --> 00:09:12,306
Commencing deployment now.

134
00:09:14,558 --> 00:09:18,103
Three, two, one, mark.

135
00:09:52,679 --> 00:09:54,515
Reinforcements! Finally!

136
00:10:14,409 --> 00:10:18,372
Anakin, I'm going to look for Senator Tills.
Hopefully she's still alive.

137
00:10:18,455 --> 00:10:19,456
Be careful.

138
00:10:19,540 --> 00:10:20,749
Look out!

139
00:10:38,267 --> 00:10:40,060
Stay down and don't move.

140
00:10:53,115 --> 00:10:55,409
Hear that? They're cheering for you.

141
00:10:55,659 --> 00:10:57,578
They're cheering for them.

142
00:10:58,036 --> 00:10:59,621
Then make it for you.

143
00:11:00,372 --> 00:11:01,707
Come on!

144
00:11:02,916 --> 00:11:03,917
Lead!

145
00:11:51,632 --> 00:11:53,008
You called for backup?

146
00:11:56,803 --> 00:12:00,849
I had it under control, Snips.

147
00:12:01,141 --> 00:12:03,101
Hah ! I knew you'd say that.

148
00:12:04,311 --> 00:12:06,146
Anakin, I need you down here.

149
00:12:06,188 --> 00:12:09,399
It's Senator Tills.
I need help getting her to safety.

150
00:12:09,483 --> 00:12:11,902
<i>We're at the base of the palace. And hurry.</i>

151
00:12:14,655 --> 00:12:17,741
Ahsoka, cover the prince.
I'm going for the Senators.

152
00:12:20,160 --> 00:12:21,536
You got it, Master.

153
00:12:35,842 --> 00:12:38,095
-Grab on !
-Good idea.

154
00:12:44,685 --> 00:12:46,186
Get us out of here!

155
00:12:46,270 --> 00:12:48,730
-Hang on !
-I am ! I am!

156
00:13:02,911 --> 00:13:03,912
I'm slipping!

157
00:13:14,715 --> 00:13:17,467
Look out! They're coming right at us!

158
00:13:18,969 --> 00:13:20,554
I'm letting go!

159
00:13:28,854 --> 00:13:31,064
Look out! Behind you!

160
00:13:33,734 --> 00:13:35,485
As long as we're in the tube we're safe.

161
00:13:45,829 --> 00:13:46,913
Look! The prince!

162
00:14:04,264 --> 00:14:05,390
Hurry!

163
00:14:13,273 --> 00:14:14,983
They are returning to their ships.

164
00:14:22,574 --> 00:14:24,951
We seem to have won this round.

165
00:14:25,077 --> 00:14:27,412
We are lucky to have survived
the first assault.

166
00:14:27,788 --> 00:14:29,873
They could've easily overrun us
with their droids.

167
00:14:30,290 --> 00:14:32,709
The droids are taking up position
in the coral.

168
00:14:32,793 --> 00:14:34,795
Probably amassing for another assault.

169
00:14:34,836 --> 00:14:37,089
Why would they hide in the coral?

170
00:14:50,769 --> 00:14:54,356
Your aqua-droids are no match
for the Mon Calamari.

171
00:14:54,439 --> 00:14:56,483
What makes you think
these secret weapons

172
00:14:56,566 --> 00:14:59,861
you've brought from your home world
will fare any better?

173
00:14:59,945 --> 00:15:02,781
They are half-machine,
half-monster.

174
00:15:02,823 --> 00:15:05,450
We call them Hydroid Medusas.

175
00:15:06,159 --> 00:15:08,120
They are invincible.

176
00:15:23,009 --> 00:15:27,347
-Prince Lee-Char!
-Senator Tills, I'm glad to see you're safe.

177
00:15:27,389 --> 00:15:31,309
You must prepare to dictate terms
for a Quarren surrender.

178
00:15:31,852 --> 00:15:34,729
-Surrender?
-Not so fast, Senator.

179
00:15:34,813 --> 00:15:37,482
I know the Quarren, they won't surrender.

180
00:15:37,899 --> 00:15:41,486
We may have won the first battle,
Your Highness, but it won't be the last.

181
00:15:41,528 --> 00:15:45,198
It's only a matter of time
before they launch another assault.

182
00:15:45,282 --> 00:15:47,784
I sense the real battle is about to begin.

183
00:16:07,596 --> 00:16:09,556
We have no defense against those.

184
00:16:09,681 --> 00:16:12,350
This isn't going to be easy.

185
00:16:16,563 --> 00:16:18,773
All troops, battle stations!

186
00:16:40,045 --> 00:16:42,923
Do not fire
until the prince gives the command.

187
00:16:51,306 --> 00:16:53,558
Steady, steady.

188
00:17:00,106 --> 00:17:01,274
Not yet.

189
00:17:13,078 --> 00:17:14,704
Now, Your Highness!

190
00:17:15,705 --> 00:17:16,957
Attack!

191
00:17:53,743 --> 00:17:55,370
Ahsoka, find a way out of here!

192
00:17:58,498 --> 00:18:00,458
Prince, where's somewhere safe?

193
00:18:00,500 --> 00:18:03,587
We can't retreat, not now.
We've got to be brave.

194
00:18:03,670 --> 00:18:06,339
There's a time to attack
and a time to retreat,

195
00:18:06,423 --> 00:18:08,425
and now is not the time to be brave.

196
00:18:09,342 --> 00:18:10,969
The safest place is in the caves.

197
00:18:11,011 --> 00:18:13,513
I agree, Your Highness, follow me.

198
00:18:18,143 --> 00:18:19,936
Anakin ! Go! I'll hold them off.

199
00:18:46,171 --> 00:18:48,632
Come on. Keep going ! Don't stop!

200
00:19:11,821 --> 00:19:13,823
Search the area for survivors.

201
00:19:15,283 --> 00:19:16,951
Secure the perimeter.

202
00:19:20,580 --> 00:19:23,083
What took your squids so long?

203
00:19:23,124 --> 00:19:27,420
I didn't think you and your Separatist
droids would need backup.

204
00:19:27,545 --> 00:19:30,674
Your reputation is a little exaggerated.

205
00:19:31,591 --> 00:19:34,344
Exaggeration is a weapon of war.

206
00:19:34,761 --> 00:19:37,514
It's what helped deliver the enemy
into your hands.

207
00:19:37,847 --> 00:19:42,977
Then let's be thankful this is our day,
a victorious day that...

208
00:19:43,103 --> 00:19:45,730
Disobey a command
from Count Dooku again

209
00:19:45,814 --> 00:19:48,983
and I will kill you where you stand.

210
00:20:17,011 --> 00:20:20,432
Thanks to you, Padawan Tano,
and to these brave soldiers.

211
00:20:20,974 --> 00:20:23,143
I wish I could've done more for my people.

212
00:20:23,184 --> 00:20:26,146
Maybe then we would've been spared
all of this,

213
00:20:26,229 --> 00:20:29,315
the illusion that I could actually lead
in my father's place.

214
00:20:29,858 --> 00:20:31,818
Your father would be proud of you.

215
00:20:32,318 --> 00:20:34,320
Proud? We lost!

216
00:20:34,779 --> 00:20:38,658
Today, you learned the hardest lesson
a commander can learn,

217
00:20:39,325 --> 00:20:41,911
how to live to fight another day.

218
00:20:41,935 --> 00:20:46,935
http://hiqve.com/

